This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition using deep convolutional neural networks. The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical aggregation design, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of the UCF101 database for experiments suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
